Data

We use the Gapminder data. The Gapminder ProjectGapminder project was pioneered by Hans Rosling, who is famous for describing the prosperity of nations over time through famines, wars and other historic events with this beautiful data visualization in his 2006 TED Talk: The best stats you’ve ever seen:

Let’s explore a subset of the data from 2011.

gap2011 <- gapminder %>% 
  as_tibble() %>% 
  filter(year == 2011)

dim(gap2011)

Life expectancy

Explore the distribution of life expectancy data

Histogram: Not very pretty.

Density plot: This is nicer.

What is the relationship between life expectancy and fertility?

Where fertility is higher, life expectancy was lower.

ggplot(data = gap2011) +
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x = fertility, y = life_expectancy, color = continent)) +
  geom_smooth(mapping = aes(x = fertility, y = life_expectancy))
